post_text:
We wanted to make you aware that United has a Remote Learning Support Page that can answer just about any question you might have about Remote Learning. If you are unable to find your answer on the support page, please feel free to click the "Submit a Remote Learning Support Request" button on the Support page. If your student has not been able to join a teacher's Google Classroom or SeeSaw Classroom, please check your student / parent emails for invites. If you don't see an invite, please let your student's teacher know as soon as possible. Staff email addresses can be found on the Remote Learning Support Page.

Click the link to go to the United Remote Learning Support Page. Have your student bookmark it if that is helpful.

https://sites.google.com/u304.org/u304remotelearning/home

post_text:
The Warren County Clerk is seeking students to serve as election judges for the November 3, 2020 General Election.
Students must be at least 17 years of age, of good character, willing to work all day (7am - 7pm), work well with others,
able to follow instructions. The student will receive payment for the day, by check after the election.
If interested please contact the Warren County Clerk's office, 309-734-4612 or come in to the County Clerk's Office.
Disclaimer: only 15-25 students from each school district may be chosen to work.
